                     Backout_Queue Creation & configuration to Application.

* MQSC Script to create Backout Queue and link it to an application input queue
* Queue Manager: QMGR_NAME (replace with your actual queue manager name)

* 1) Define the Backout Queue (BOQ)
DEFINE QLOCAL(APP.BOQ) DESCR('Backout Queue for APP.INPUT.Q') MAXDEPTH(5000) MAXMSGL(10485760) DEFPSIST(YES)

* 2) Define the Application Input Queue and link BOQ
DEFINE QLOCAL(APP.INPUT.Q) +
       DESCR('Application Input Queue') MAXDEPTH(5000) MAXMSGL(10485760) DEFPSIST(YES) BOQNAME(APP.BOQ) BOQTHRESH(3)
IF u already created APPlication QUEUE 

ALTER QLOCAL(APP.INPUT.Q) BOQNAME(APP.BOQ) BOQTHRESH(3)

* 3) Display queues to verify configuration
DISPLAY QLOCAL(APP.INPUT.Q) BOQNAME BOQTHRESH

DISPLAY QLOCAL(APP.BOQ)

* Notes:
* - BOQTHRESH(3) means after 3 failed attempts, message moves to BOQ.
* - Adjust MAXDEPTH and MAXMSGL as per your environment.
* - Ensure application logic handles messages from BOQ (e.g., error handling or manual intervention).
